            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 1
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT I  -  THE DROWNED MIRE"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   They say a star fell on Aelthmoor and the castle drank it. They say the"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Mirewood grew to seal the wound. You go where the saying ends."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 2
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT II  -  THE BROKEN BARBICAN"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The bog is behind you; the first real stone is not. Caer Vodran's outer"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   wall still stands its watch, though nothing living mans it."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 3
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT III  -  THE FLOODED WARDS"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Inside the wall, the courts lie under black water to the knee. The garrison"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   drowned at its posts an age ago, and has not yet noticed."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 4
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT IV  -  THE HOLLOW HALLS"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The keep proper. Banners rot, hearths are cold, and the halls are not empty -"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   they are occupied, by everything they used to be, hollowed and humming."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 5
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT V  -  THE SUNKEN ARCHIVE"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Down into the drowned library, where the kingdom kept what it knew of the star."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The water here is more ink than water, and the ink has opinions."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 6
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT VI  -  THE ASH BARRACKS"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The garrison that held the inner keep never stood down, never burned out -"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   it only banked itself in ash, and waits in ranks for an order that never came."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 7
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT VII  -  THE CHAPEL OF THE CHOIR"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Here the court tried to pray the whisper away, and the whisper answered."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   It took their voices first, and then the rest of them, one held note at a time."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 8
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT VIII  -  THE STAR-CRYPT"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Below the chapel the stone gives way to black crystal that remembers being sky."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   A shard of the fallen star is buried here, and it is not buried deeply enough."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 9
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT IX  -  THE WHISPERING DEEP"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The whisper is a wind now, and it has learned your cadence, your name, your face."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Down here, your own thoughts answer you - and they are not always on your side."
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 10
                TALK TO THE HAND "   ACT X  -  THE VAULT OF THE CROWN"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Below the foundations the stone goes warm and the angles go wrong."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The whisper has a direction now. It is down. It has always been down."
        FINISH HIM
