                    CHOOSE YOUR DESTINY LOOK AT ME.act
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 1
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   A surveyor's ghost mutters of a star that fell before the maps were drawn,"
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   and a king who paid his masons in silence to wall the light away."
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 2
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   Scratched into the gate-stone: 'We held three years. The thing inside held longer.'"
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   The hand that carved it stopped mid-word."
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 3
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   A drowned ledger lists the garrison's dead by the hundred, then simply: 'all'."
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   The final entry is your own name, in a hand you do not recognize."
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 4
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   The banners name battles no history remembers, against an enemy with no name -"
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   only a direction. Down. The court marched down, and did not march back."
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 5
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   A scholar's note, the ink still wet after centuries: 'The Crown tells no lies.'"
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   'That is the horror of it. Every promise it makes, it keeps.'"
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 6
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   The muster-roll still calls the watch each dusk, and the ash still answers."
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   They were promised relief at dawn. No dawn has come to the Barracks since."
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 7
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   The choir's first hymn was a prayer; the second, a bargain; the third had no words -"
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   by then the singers had given the Crown their voices to hold for safekeeping."
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 8
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   The star did not fall by accident, the crystals sing. It was thrown - or it leapt."
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   Something wanted to be buried here. Something is still glad that it is."
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 9
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   The whisper tries on your memories like coats: your first kill, your last fear."
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   It wears them better than you do, and asks, gently, why you came so far to die."
                        WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 10
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   This close, the Crown's voice is your own, older and certain and kind:"
                            TALK TO THE HAND "   'You could put me on. You could end the descent. You could simply stop being afraid.'"
