            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 0
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The reeds part on a ring of standing roots. They knot together, rise,"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   and take up a crown of black thorn and a drowned knight's rusted arms."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   THE MIRE-WARDEN wakes to keep a watch older than the kingdom."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 1
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The half-fallen portcullis grinds. The gatehouse stone itself stands up,"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   iron grate for a face, a century of siege ground into its fists."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   THE GATE-GOLEM bars the way, as it was built and broken to do."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 2
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   A knight stands waist-deep in the flooded ward, water pouring endlessly"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   from the joints of his armor. He does not breathe; he has not, in an age."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   SIR CAEDRIC, last captain of the wards, lifts a blade gone green with rot."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 3
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The gallery is empty, but the air is crowded. Every step you have taken"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   comes back wrong, and the wrongness gathers into a shape made of sound -"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   THE ECHO, the hall's memory of every soldier who ever screamed here."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 4
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Among the drowned stacks, the spilled ink of ten thousand books has"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   learned to stand. It wears a reader's robe and a face of running text,"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   THE INK-WRAITH, the Archive's last and maddest librarian."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 5
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The muster yard rings with a horn that has no horn. From the cot-rows of"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   grey ash rises a captain in fused armor, his garrison forming up behind."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   CAPTAIN VURM never stood down, and will not, until you make him."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 6
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   A hundred hollow mouths hum one endless note. At the altar floats MAERITH,"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   once Archmage of Aelthmoor, now a chorus of stolen voices wearing her shape."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   She turns her eyeless face toward you, and the choir inhales."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 7
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The geode sings at your heartbeat. Then the crystal answers with its own,"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   tearing free of the walls into a thing of black glass and trapped starlight."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   THE CRYSTALLINE HORROR unfolds, refracting a hundred wrong reflections of you."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 8
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   Something steps out of the still black water wearing your face, your scars,"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   your blade - and your every habit of fighting, learned by watching you fall."
                TALK TO THE HAND "   THE MIRROR smiles with your mouth and says your name in the whisper's voice."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
            WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 9
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
                TALK TO THE HAND "   The vault is a wound in the world. At its center turns the Sunken Crown:"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   a fallen star folded into a ring of black gold, whispering your name in a"
                TALK TO THE HAND "   voice you have always known. VODRAN opens like an eye, and the dark leans in."
                TALK TO THE HAND ""
