                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 0
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The Warden sloughs apart into wet timber and old steel."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   Where its heart should be, a cold seed pulses once, then stills."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   Beyond the roots, the first true stone of Caer Vodran stands waiting."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 1
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The golem comes apart at its old fracture lines, slab by slab,"
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   and settles into rubble that finally stops pretending to be a wall."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The inner courts lie open, ankle-deep in black water."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 2
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   Caedric sinks to one knee, and the water finally takes him under for good."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   His blade slips from a hand that seems, for a moment, almost grateful."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   A cold stair winds deeper, into the castle's hollowed heart."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 3
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The Echo comes apart into a hundred fading cries, then silence -"
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   a real silence, the first this hall has held in a hundred years."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   Drowned shelves and floating pages glimmer in the dark below."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 4
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The wraith unspools into a slick of black water and ruined words"
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   that finally, mercifully, mean nothing at all."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   A cartographer's vault gapes beyond, hung with maps of a lost sky."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 5
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   Vurm salutes - whether you or some long-dead king, you cannot tell -"
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   and crumbles, and his soldiers with him, back into quiet ash."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   A nave opens ahead, holding one long, breathless note."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 6
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The choir falls silent, voice by voice, until only Maerith remains -"
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   and then she, too, unravels into drifting motes of cold light."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The stone past the altar turns to black glass, and remembers the sky."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 7
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The Horror shatters into a slow rain of singing glass that dims, and dies."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   In the quiet after, a single shard of true star-stuff floats, waiting."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   Below, the whisper takes on a voice you know far too well."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 8
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   You strike the blow you would never have seen coming, because it is yours."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The Mirror cracks, and the thing behind your face flees back into the dark."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   Only the Last Stair remains, warm and faintly breathing, leading down."
                    WHAT IF I TOLD YOU 9
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   You drive the final blow into the heart of the star. The whisper"
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   stutters, climbs to a shriek - and goes out, like a candle pinched cold."
                        TALK TO THE HAND "   The Mirewood exhales. Far above, for the first time in an age, it is morning."
